<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40028b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40028b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40028b"> 28(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> an untouchable</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;I once went near to the shelter of <mark>an &lsquo;untouchable&rsquo;</mark> in Malabar,&rdquo; says Mr. C. F. Andrews in &ldquo;Christ and Labour,&rdquo; &mdash; &ldquo;it could not even be called a hovel it was so wretchedly made.&rdquo; &ldquo;As I approached,&rdquo; he adds, &ldquo;the shrinking fear was so abject and the cries of miserable fright were so piteous that I simply dare not approach nearer, though I had come on an errand of love.&rdquo; <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI1"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
